		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />FRAM is a drop-in replacement for battery-backed SRAM.  They could use either on the same board.  I have an FRAM chip that I tried on Squeedo, and it works.  It's a shame the 5V version doesn't have infinite endurance though.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


